String Functions for Formula Fields
Use string functions to create values in a formula field based on one or more dimension columns in your recipe or strings.
concat Function
Returns a string by concatenating the values of the specified columns and input strings.
lower Function
Returns a string with all characters from the input string in lowercase.
ltrim Function
Removes the specified substring from the beginning of a string.
replace Function
Replaces a substring with the specified characters.
rtrim Function
Removes the specified substring from the end of a string.
substr Function
Returns characters from the string, starting at the specified position and of the specified length.
title Function
Returns the string with the initial character of every word in uppercase and the remaining characters in lowercase.
trim Function
Removes the specified substring from the beginning and end of a string.
upper Function

You can use a formula to manipulate strings, instead of dataflow transformations, to perform multiple string manipulations at the same time.

title(concat([Sales_Territory], " ",[Country]))

When entering a formula, text strings must be enclosed in double straight quotes ("This is a string."). Column names must be enclosed in square brackets ([Opportunity_Name]).
title: Manipulating Strings with Salesforce CRM Analytics
